    <item>
      <title>Pondering plywood</title>
      <link>https://boat.karlnelson.net/posts/51-plywood/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Nov 2024 09:00:00 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://boat.karlnelson.net/posts/51-plywood/</guid>
      <description>The next big step in the boat project is buying the plywood that will be used to construct the hull.
There&amp;rsquo;s a few things to note about the plywood:
This isn&amp;rsquo;t the stuff you buy at the big box store. It&amp;rsquo;s marine-grade plywood, which is higher quality and more expensive than the normal stuff. The plywood gets CNC cut – think: a computer that controls a router to cut out precise shapes.</description>
