    <item>
      <title>Eight-sided gaff</title>
      <link>https://boat.karlnelson.net/posts/11-eight-sided-gaff/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 22 Oct 2022 19:00:00 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://boat.karlnelson.net/posts/11-eight-sided-gaff/</guid>
      <description>With the lines drawn using the spar gauge, it was time to knock off the corners and go from a four-sided stick to an eight-sided stick.
To do that, I first needed to make some jigs to hold the spar in place. I picked up a 2x6, cut off four pieces, then used a little bandsaw (checked out from the tool library) to cut notches in the pieces. I also shaped them so they&amp;rsquo;d be easy to clamp down to the table, and made another little notch so I could clamp a piece across the top to hold the spar down.</description>
